__more"><a href="/videos" class="video__end-slate__replay-text">More Videos ...</a></div></div></div></div><h4 class="video__end-slate__tertiary-title">MUST WATCH</h4><div class="js-video__end-slate__tertiary video__end-slate__tertiary"><div class="js-video__end-slate__carousel video__end-slate__carousel"></div></div></div></div><script type="application/ld+json" name="metaScript">{"@context": "http://schema.org","@type": "VideoObject","name": "Bernie Fest: Can Sanders start a revolution?","description": "Meet the masses rooting for Vermont&#39;s Democratic presidential candidate Bernie Sanders.","thumbnailURL": "http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/150527172720-woman-at-sanders-kick-off-rally-large-169.jpg","image": "http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/150527172720-woman-at-sanders-kick-off-rally-large-169.jpg","duration": "PT1M53S","uploadDate": "2015-05-28T09:47:56Z","contentUrl": "http://www.cnn.com/videos/politics/2015/05/27/bernie-sanders-2016-kickoff-rally.cnn","url": "http://www.cnn.com/videos/politics/2015/05/27/bernie-sanders-2016-kickoff-rally.cnn"}</script><div id="body-text_6" class="media__video--responsive " data-video-id="politics/2015/05/27/bernie-sanders-2016-kickoff-rally.cnn"></div><div id="body-text_6-metadata" class="metadata"><p class="metadata__source"><span class="metadata__source-name"></span></p></div></div><div class="media__caption el__storyelement__title"><span class="el__storyelement__header">Bernie Fest: Can Sanders start a revolution?</span> <span class="el__storyelement__gray">01:52</span></div></div></div></div><div class="zn-body__paragraph"><a href="http://www.cnn.com/2015/05/28/politics/bernie-sanders-presidential-campaign-revolution/index.html">RELATED: Will Bernie Sanders start a revolution?</a></div><div class="zn-body__read-more"><div class="read-more-gradient"></div><div class="read-more-button"><div class="read-more-link" id="js-body-read-more">Read More</div></div></div><div class="zn-body__read-all"><div class="zn-body__paragraph">The 1972 essay, which was <a href="http://www.motherjones.com/politics/2015/05/young-bernie-sanders-liberty-union-vermont" target="_blank">first revealed in a profile by Mother Jones</a>, was published in the Vermont Freeman, an alternative newspaper from Sanders' home state. It ran the same year that Sanders ran for governor of the state as a member of the anti-Vietnam War Liberty Union Party. He lost the race, but was elected mayor of Burlington in 1981.</div><div class="zn-body__paragraph">"Have you looked at the Stag, Man, Hero, Tough magazines on the shelf of your local bookstores? Do you know why the newspapers with articles like 'Girl, 12, raped by 14 men' sell so well?" Sanders wrote. "To what in us are they appealing?"</div><div class="el__embedded el__embedded--fullwidth"><div class="el__image--fullwidth js__image--fullwidth"><div><img class="media__image media__image--responsive" alt="" data-src-mini="http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/150528170109-bernie-sanders-man-woman-essay-lead-05-28-small-169.jpg" data-src-xsmall="http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/150528170109-bernie-sanders-man-woman-essay-lead-05-28-medium-plus-169.jpg" data-src-small="http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/150528170109-bernie-sanders-man-woman-essay-lead-05-28-large-169.jpg" data-src-medium="http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/150528170109-bernie-sanders-man-woman-essay-lead-05-28-exlarge-169.jpg" data-src-large="http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/150528170109-bernie-sanders-man-woman-essay-lead-05-28-super-169.jpg" data-src-full16x9="http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/150528170109-bernie-sanders-man-woman-essay-lead-05-28-full-169.jpg" data-src-mini1x1="http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/150528170109-bernie-sanders-man-woman-essay-lead-05-28-small-11.jpg"  data-demand-load="not-loaded" data-eq-pts="mini: 0,  xsmall: 221,  small: 308,  medium: 461,  large:  781" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhEAAJAJEAAAAAAP///////wAAACH5BAEAAAIALAAAAAAQAAkAAAIKlI+py+0Po5yUFQA7"><div class="img__preloader"></div><noscript><img alt="" class="media__image" src="http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/150528170109-bernie-sanders-man-woman-essay-lead-05-28-large-169.jpg"></noscript></div></div></div><div class="zn-body__paragraph">The article also says that a man's "typical fantasy" of a woman includes her "tied up" and "abused."</div><div class="zn-body__paragraph">Sanders analyzes the dynamics of sexuality and relationship between men and women, including a seemingly made up conversation between a couple about their deteriorating relationship. </div><div class="zn-body__paragraph">"And they never again made love together (which they had each liked to do more than anything) or never ever saw each other one more time," he wrote.</div><div class="zn-body__paragraph">In the statement, Briggs said that the essay surfaced as a result of Sanders' presidential ambitions.</div><div class="el__embedded el__embedded--fullstandardwidth"><div class="el__gallery--fullstandardwidth js__gallery--fullstandardwidth js__leafmedia--gallery"><div class="el-carousel__wrapper"><div class=" js-owl-carousel owl-carousel carousel--full body" data-galleryname="Bernie Sanders in the spotlight" data-cut-format="16:9" data-is-gallery="true" data-slide-count="23"><div data-slidename="Bernie Sanders in the spotlight" data-analytics="_body_image"><div class="el__resize"><div class="el__position media js-gallery-aspect-ratio-wrapper"><img class="media__image media__image--responsive media__image--cut-format" alt="U.S. Sen. Bernie Sanders, an independent from Vermont, is battling Hillary Clinton for the Democratic Party&amp;#39;s presidential nomination. He is the longest-serving independent in the history of Congress." data-src-mini="http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/160222103319-01-bernie-sanders-small-169.jpg" data-src-xsmall="http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/160222103319-01-ber